error: adding an unchecked value to a pointer takes it out of bounds
   |
 9 |     int pos = bpf_strstr(req, "GET ");
   |               ---------- this value is unchecked here (it can be negative — e.g. -1 when a search fails)
10 |     return req[pos];
   |            ^^^ offset may be negative or too large here
   |
help: check the value before indexing, e.g. `if (i < 0 || i >= sizeof(buf)) return 0;`